# Phase 6: Approval Workflow Engine

This plan details the implementation of an Approval Workflow Engine that restricts high-risk operations from executing immediately, forcing them through a review cycle (Pending -> Approved -> Rejected).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The threshold for a "High Discount" must be defined. For this implementation, I propose intercepting any price change where the `price` is less than 80% of the `mrp` (a 20%+ discount) if performed by a staff member. Please let me know if you prefer a different threshold.

## Proposed Architecture

### 1. The Approvals Collection
We will utilize a new Firebase collection named `approvals`. 
- **Schema**: `id`, `type`, `status` (pending, approved, rejected), `storeId`, `requestedBy` (userId), `requestedRole`, `payload` (the data to execute), `timestamp`, `reviewedBy`, `comments`.

### 2. The Core Engine
#### [NEW] [useApprovals.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useApprovals.js)
- A new hook that provides `submitApprovalRequest(type, payload)` and `processApproval(id, status)`.
- It will also export a real-time list of `pendingApprovals` for the active store so managers can review them.

### 3. Intercepting High-Risk Actions
We will update our existing hooks to check the active user's role. If the user is `staff`, the action will be redirected to `submitApprovalRequest` instead of executing directly.

#### [MODIFY] [useProducts.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useProducts.js)
- **Product Deletion**: Always requires approval for staff.
- **High Discounts**: Check if `updateData.price` represents a significant discount compared to `mrp`. If so, require approval.

#### [MODIFY] [useInventory.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useInventory.js)
- **Inventory Adjustments**: Redirect `updateStock` calls to approvals if initiated by staff.
- **Stock Transfers**: Redirect `addStockTransfer` calls to approvals.

#### [MODIFY] [useFinance.js](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/hooks/useFinance.js)
- **Finance Adjustments**: Redirect `addTransaction` and `addExpense`.
- **Vendor Payments**: Redirect `addVendorPayment`.

#### Vendor Creation
- We will locate the Vendor creation logic and intercept it similarly.

### 4. Manager/Admin Review Interface
#### [NEW] [ApprovalDashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/praga/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/jewellery-website/src/admin/pages/ApprovalDashboard.jsx) or modifying an existing view.
- We need a place for Managers to review these pending requests. I will add an "Approvals" tab to the dashboard or integrate it into an existing page (e.g., a unified Notifications/Approvals drop-down, or an Approvals page).

## Verification Plan
1. Log in as a `staff` member and attempt to delete a product.
2. Verify that the product is NOT deleted, but a new `Approval Request` is created.
3. Log in as a `manager` and approve the request.
4. Verify that the product is then actually deleted.
